content.description:
To the right of the 'Inside Corner' dihedral that is in the BB. Don’t see a name for this one anywhere so I made one up.

Start in a jug at the bottom of the right less pronounced dihedral feature, and enjoy the beautiful views as you ascend on nice holds. It’s all pretty reasonable, just a little blind reaching for holds around the bulge at the top, but there are some nice ones up there.
content.protection: 3-4 pads and a spotter or two, landing is odd and top leans out a bit
content.location: On the right side of the west face of the Dice Cube Boulder

content.description: Start in some decent holds at the bottom of the dihedral in the middle of the west face, and move up to a dicey topout that is worse than it looks. There is a bolt on the top of the boulder if you want to dial it in with a rope.
content.protection: 4-5 pads to level it out, and a spotter or two
content.location: Middle of the west face of the Dice Cube.
